Introduction

Jung Wooseok is a South Korean rapper, singer-songwriter, and the main rapper, vocalist, and maknae of PENTAGON. Known for his deep voice and tall stature, he has collaborated with various artists, including Soyeon of (G)I-DLE and Lai Kuanlin.

Wooseok debuted with PENTAGON on October 10, 2016, with the mini-album PENTAGON. On March 11, 2019, he debuted in the unit Wooseok X Kuanlin alongside former Wanna One member Lai Kuanlin, releasing the EP 9801 and the title track I'm A Star.

In 2020, he participated in the rap competition show Show Me the Money 9 but was eliminated during the 60-Second Team Trials. Despite this, he remains active as a rapper and performer in the industry.
